SIMPLE: orientate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orientate
<hw>O"ri*en*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Orientated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Orientating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<er>Orient</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To place or turn toward the east; to cause to assume
an easterly direction, or to veer eastward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To arrange in order; to dispose or place (a body) so
as to show its relation to other bodies, or the relation of its parts
among themselves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A crystal is <qex>orientated</qex> when placed in its proper
position so as to exhibit its symmetry.</q> <rj><qau>E. S.
Dana.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>orient</er>{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orientate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Orientate
<hw>O"ri*en*tate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To move or turn toward the
east; to veer from the north or south toward the east.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oriented</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>orientated</ent>⟦br⟧
